\p
\v 37 “\w The|strong="G2532"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w more|strong="G5228"\w* devoted \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w father|strong="G3962"\w* \w or|strong="G2228"\w* \w mother|strong="G3384"\w* \w than|strong="G2228"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* worthy \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w more|strong="G5228"\w* devoted \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w son|strong="G5207"\w* \w or|strong="G2228"\w* \w daughter|strong="G2364"\w* \w than|strong="G2228"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* worthy \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*;  
\v 38 \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w does|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w take|strong="G2983"\w* \w up|strong="G2532"\w* \w his|strong="G2983"\w* \w cross|strong="G4716"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w follow|strong="G3694"\w* \w after|strong="G3694"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* worthy \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*.\f + \fr 10:38 \ft Notice that it is Jesus who sets the parameters, not we. Rather than people ‘accepting’ Jesus, the question is whether He will accept us.\f*  
\v 39 \w The|strong="G2532"\w* \w one|strong="G1438"\w* ‘\w finding|strong="G2147"\w*’ \w his|strong="G1438"\w* \w life|strong="G5590"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* lose \w it|strong="G2532"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w one|strong="G1438"\w* ‘losing’ \w his|strong="G1438"\w* \w life|strong="G5590"\w* \w for|strong="G1752"\w* \w my|strong="G1473"\w* \w sake|strong="G1752"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w find|strong="G2147"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w*.\f + \fr 10:39 \ft I take it that the reference is to the potential that your life represents, potential in the interests of God's Kingdom. To the extent that your life revolves around God's will and Kingdom you will both find and save it—of course from the world's perspective you will be throwing it away.\f*   
\p
\v 40 “\w The|strong="G2532"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* receiving \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w receives|strong="G1209"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* receiving \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w receives|strong="G1209"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w One|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w sent|strong="G2532"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*.  
\v 41 \w The|strong="G2532"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w receiving|strong="G2983"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w prophet|strong="G4396"\w* \w in|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w prophet|strong="G4396"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w receive|strong="G2983"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w prophet|strong="G4396"\w*'s \w reward|strong="G3408"\w*,\f + \fr 10:41 \ft I assume that the point here is identification: you are identifying with the prophet whose name you invoke; and if that prophet is in prison, you are taking a risk.\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w receiving|strong="G2983"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w righteous|strong="G1342"\w* \w man|strong="G1342"\w* \w in|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w righteous|strong="G1342"\w* \w man|strong="G1342"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w receive|strong="G2983"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w righteous|strong="G1342"\w* \w man|strong="G1342"\w*'s \w reward|strong="G3408"\w*.  
\v 42 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w whoever|strong="G3739"\w* \w should|strong="G3588"\w* \w give|strong="G4222"\w* \w so|strong="G2532"\w* much \w as|strong="G1519"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w cup|strong="G4221"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w cold|strong="G5593"\w* \it water\it* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w one|strong="G1520"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w these|strong="G3778"\w* \w little|strong="G3398"\w* \w ones|strong="G3398"\w*, \w in|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w disciple|strong="G3101"\w*, assuredly \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w say|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*, \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w certainly|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* lose \w his|strong="G1519"\w* \w reward|strong="G3408"\w*.”\f + \fr 10:42 \ft Presumably the rewards mentioned here are received in this life, since the good deeds mentioned could be performed by an unbeliever. I suggest that God blesses anyone who takes sides with what is right, good, decent, honorable, just—but if that person does not belong to Christ the blessing is limited to this life.\f*   
\c 11  
\ms1 The Pharisees reject Jesus as Messiah  
\m
\v 1 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w so|strong="G2532"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G1096"\w*, \w when|strong="G3753"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w finished|strong="G5055"\w* directing \w His|strong="G1722"\w* \w twelve|strong="G1427"\w* \w disciples|strong="G3101"\w*, \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* moved \w on|strong="G1722"\w* \w from|strong="G2532"\w* \w there|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w teach|strong="G1321"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w preach|strong="G2784"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w their|strong="G2532"\w* \w towns|strong="G4172"\w*.   
\s1 John needs reassuring  
\p
\v 2 \w But|strong="G1161"\w* \w John|strong="G2491"\w*, hearing \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w prison|strong="G1201"\w* \it about\it* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w works|strong="G2041"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Messiah|strong="G5547"\w*, \w sent|strong="G3992"\w* two \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w his|strong="G1223"\w* \w disciples|strong="G3101"\w*  
\v 3 \w to|strong="G3004"\w* \w say|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G3004"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*, “\w Are|strong="G1510"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w Coming|strong="G2064"\w* \w One|strong="G3588"\w*, \w or|strong="G2228"\w* \w do|strong="G3004"\w* \w we|strong="G1510"\w* \w look|strong="G4328"\w* \w for|strong="G4328"\w* \w another|strong="G2087"\w*?”\f + \fr 11:3 \ft John was in prison, which was contrary to his expectations; like all the others he expected Jesus to set up the Kingdom right then. In answer the Lord says, in effect, that the Kingdom is not based on our expectations.\f*  
\v 4 \w By|strong="G2532"\w* \w way|strong="G4198"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* answer \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*: “\w Go|strong="G4198"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* report \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w John|strong="G2491"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w things|strong="G3588"\w* \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w you|strong="G3739"\w* hear \w and|strong="G2532"\w* see:  
\v 5 \w blind|strong="G5185"\w* regain sight \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w lame|strong="G5560"\w* \w walk|strong="G4043"\w*, \w lepers|strong="G3015"\w* \w are|strong="G2532"\w* \w cleansed|strong="G2511"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w deaf|strong="G2974"\w* hear, \w dead|strong="G3498"\w* \w are|strong="G2532"\w* \w raised|strong="G1453"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w poor|strong="G4434"\w* \w are|strong="G2532"\w* evangelized.  
\v 6 \w And|strong="G2532"\w*, \w blessed|strong="G3107"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w whoever|strong="G3739"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w offended|strong="G4624"\w* \w at|strong="G1722"\w* \nd \+w Me|strong="G1473"\+w*\nd*!”\f + \fr 11:6 \ft Verse 6 was directed specifically at John. When Jesus went to John to be baptized, John knew perfectly well that he was looking at the Messiah, but now, because of his circumstances, he is in doubt. In effect, Jesus is saying, “Whatever you do, do not rebel!” And He is still saying so to us: when your circumstances are painful and unexplained, do not rebel!\f*   
\s1 Jesus commends John the Baptizer  
\p
\v 7 \w So|strong="G1161"\w* \w as|strong="G1519"\w* \w they|strong="G1161"\w* \w departed|strong="G1831"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w began|strong="G1161"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w say|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G1519"\w* \w crowds|strong="G3793"\w* \w concerning|strong="G4012"\w* \w John|strong="G2491"\w*: “\w What|strong="G5101"\w* \w did|strong="G5101"\w* \w you|strong="G3004"\w* \w go|strong="G4198"\w* \w out|strong="G1831"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G1519"\w* \w wilderness|strong="G2048"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w see|strong="G2300"\w*, \w a|strong="G1519"\w* \w reed|strong="G2563"\w* \w shaken|strong="G4531"\w* \w by|strong="G5259"\w* \w the|strong="G1519"\w* wind?  
