\q2 \w foal|strong="G5207"\w* \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w beast|strong="G5268"\w* \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w burden|strong="G5268"\w*.’ ”\f + \fr 21:5 \ft The quote is from Zechariah 9:9. Unfortunately the KJV (corrected by the NKJV) mistranslates both the Hebrew and the Greek, making it appear that Jesus rode both animals, which was not the case; He rode only the colt. For a more complete discussion, please see the Appendix: How many animals?\f*   
