\v 10 \w Neither|strong="G3366"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w called|strong="G2564"\w* \w leaders|strong="G3754"\w*/guides; \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w your|strong="G3366"\w* \w Leader|strong="G2519"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \nd \+w one|strong="G1520"\+w*\nd*, \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*.\f + \fr 23:10 \ft This may be why we have no record in Scripture of a Christian calling someone his disciple; even in 1 Corinthians 3:4 Paul evidently avoids using the term. I take it that our Lord is forbidding any effort by one Christian to control the spiritual life of another. He had already told the Samaritan woman that the Father must be worshiped “in spirit and truth” (John 4:23-24). Therefore, that worship may not be forced or imposed, or controlled by someone else.\f*  
\v 11 \w On|strong="G1161"\w* \w the|strong="G1161"\w* contrary, \w the|strong="G1161"\w* \w greatest|strong="G3173"\w* \w among|strong="G3588"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w must|strong="G1510"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w your|strong="G3588"\w* \w servant|strong="G1249"\w*.  
\v 12 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w whoever|strong="G3748"\w* \w exalts|strong="G5312"\w* \w himself|strong="G1438"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w humbled|strong="G5013"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w whoever|strong="G3748"\w* \w humbles|strong="G5013"\w* \w himself|strong="G1438"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w exalted|strong="G5312"\w*.   
\ms1 A series of ‘Woes’  
\p
\v 13 “\w Woe|strong="G3759"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w scribes|strong="G1122"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w Pharisees|strong="G5330"\w*, \w hypocrites|strong="G5273"\w*! \w Because|strong="G3754"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* devour \w the|strong="G2532"\w* houses \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* widows,\f + \fr 23:13 \ft How did that work? I suppose that if the widow was in debt, they would just foreclose and put her out on the street.\f* \w while|strong="G1161"\w* \w making|strong="G2532"\w* \w long|strong="G3756"\w* prayers \w as|strong="G1161"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* pretense. \w Therefore|strong="G1161"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* receive \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w greater|strong="G4771"\w* condemnation.\f + \fr 23:13 \ft They are already condemned, but are making it worse. Perhaps 2% of the Greek manuscripts, of inferior quality, omit this verse (as in NIV, [NASB], LB, [TEV], etc.). A very small minority, perhaps another 1%, reverse the order of verses 13 and 14 (as in KJV and NKJV).\f*  
\v 14 Woe to you scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites!! Because you bar \it the entrance to\it* the kingdom of the heavens in the face of the people; for you neither go in \it yourselves\it* nor do you allow those who are trying to enter to go in.\f + \fr 23:14 \ft Those guys were really perverse! If you don't want to go in yourself, that's your problem; but to try to keep others from going in is satanic, really and truly satanic.\f*  
\v 15 \w Woe|strong="G3759"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w scribes|strong="G1122"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w Pharisees|strong="G5330"\w*, \w hypocrites|strong="G5273"\w*!!! \w Because|strong="G3754"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w travel|strong="G4013"\w* \w all|strong="G2532"\w* \w over|strong="G1096"\w*, \w land|strong="G3584"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w sea|strong="G2281"\w*, \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w make|strong="G4160"\w* \w one|strong="G1520"\w* \w convert|strong="G4339"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w when|strong="G3752"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* joins \w up|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w make|strong="G4160"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w* \w twice|strong="G1362"\w* \w as|strong="G2532"\w* \w much|strong="G1362"\w* \w a|strong="G1096"\w* \w son|strong="G5207"\w* \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w Hell|strong="G1067"\w*\f + \fr 23:15 \ft Where do you suppose a ‘son of hell’ is going to spend eternity?\f* \w as|strong="G2532"\w* \w yourselves|strong="G4771"\w*.   
\p
\v 16 “\w Woe|strong="G3759"\w* \w to|strong="G3004"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w blind|strong="G5185"\w* \w guides|strong="G3595"\w*, \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w say|strong="G3004"\w*, ‘\w Whoever|strong="G3739"\w* \w swears|strong="G3660"\w* \w by|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w temple|strong="G3485"\w*, \w it|strong="G1161"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w nothing|strong="G3762"\w*; \w but|strong="G1161"\w* \w whoever|strong="G3739"\w* \w swears|strong="G3660"\w* \w by|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w gold|strong="G5557"\w* \w of|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w temple|strong="G3485"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w obligated|strong="G3784"\w*.’  
