\s2 Snakes!  
\p
\v 33 “\w Snakes|strong="G3789"\w*! \w Brood|strong="G1081"\w* \w of|strong="G3588"\w* \w vipers|strong="G2191"\w*! \w How|strong="G4459"\w* \w can|strong="G4459"\w* \w you|strong="G4459"\w* \w escape|strong="G5343"\w* \w from|strong="G3588"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w condemnation|strong="G2920"\w* \w of|strong="G3588"\w* \w Hell|strong="G1067"\w*?\f + \fr 23:33 \ft Would you say that Jesus is trying real hard not to hurt their poor little feelings? So are we supposed to avoid hurting people's feelings? When and why?\f*  
\v 34 \w So|strong="G2532"\w* \w take|strong="G2532"\w* note: \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* send \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w prophets|strong="G4396"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w wise|strong="G4680"\w* \w men|strong="G3778"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* Biblical scholars;\f + \fr 23:34 \ft Jesus makes this statement knowing that He will die within a few days. Obviously He also knows that He will rise from the dead and return to the Father's right hand—it is from that position that He will do the sending.\f* \w some|strong="G3588"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* kill, \w even|strong="G2532"\w* \w crucify|strong="G4717"\w*; \w some|strong="G3588"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w flog|strong="G3146"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w your|strong="G1223"\w* \w synagogues|strong="G4864"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w persecute|strong="G1377"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w city|strong="G4172"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w city|strong="G4172"\w*  
\v 35 —\w so|strong="G2532"\w* \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w upon|strong="G1909"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w come|strong="G2064"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w righteous|strong="G1342"\w* blood \w shed|strong="G1632"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w earth|strong="G1093"\w*, \w from|strong="G2064"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* blood \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w righteous|strong="G1342"\w* Abel \w up|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* blood \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w Zechariah|strong="G2197"\w* \w son|strong="G5207"\w* \w of|strong="G5207"\w* Berechiah,\f + \fr 23:35 \ft The only ‘Zechariah son of Berechiah’ recorded in the OT was the author of the book of prophecy that bears his name. The temple was rebuilt during his time, so it would be possible for him to have been killed there, but his death is not recorded. The Lord may have known something we do not, or He may have been referring to someone else.\f* \w whom|strong="G3739"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w murdered|strong="G5407"\w* \w between|strong="G3342"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w temple|strong="G3485"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w altar|strong="G2379"\w*.\f + \fr 23:35 \ft A terrible statement! But Jesus is addressing persons who will condemn the Messiah to death with total premeditated malice.\f*  
\v 36 Assuredly \w I|strong="G3778"\w* \w say|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G1909"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w these|strong="G3778"\w* \w things|strong="G3956"\w* \w will|strong="G3956"\w* \w come|strong="G2240"\w* \w upon|strong="G1909"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w generation|strong="G1074"\w*.   
\s1 Jesus laments over Jerusalem  
\p
