\c 24  
\ms1 The Olivet Discourse  
\m
\v 1 \w So|strong="G2532"\w* \w as|strong="G2532"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w going|strong="G4198"\w* \w out|strong="G1831"\w*, \w departing|strong="G1831"\w* \w from|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w temple|strong="G2413"\w*, \w His|strong="G2532"\w* \w disciples|strong="G3101"\w* \w came|strong="G4334"\w* \w up|strong="G4334"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w show|strong="G1925"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w buildings|strong="G3619"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w temple|strong="G2413"\w*.  
\v 2 \w But|strong="G1161"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G3004"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G1909"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*: “\w Do|strong="G3004"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* see \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w these|strong="G3778"\w* \w things|strong="G3956"\w*? Assuredly \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w say|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G1909"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*, absolutely \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w a|strong="G1909"\w* single \w stone|strong="G3037"\w* \w here|strong="G5602"\w* \w will|strong="G3739"\w* \w be|strong="G3756"\w* left \w upon|strong="G1909"\w* \w another|strong="G3037"\w*, \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w will|strong="G3739"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w be|strong="G3756"\w* thrown \w down|strong="G2647"\w*.”\f + \fr 24:2 \ft This was literally fulfilled in 70 AD. The Jews used the temple buildings as their last bastion of defense. They themselves set fire to some buildings and the Roman soldiers finished the job. Apparently the gold on the dome melted and ran down the cracks between the stones. So the looters literally tore stone from stone to make sure they got all the gold.\f*   
\s1 “A beginning of birth pains”  
\p
\v 3 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w as|strong="G1161"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w sitting|strong="G2521"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Mount|strong="G3735"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w Olives|strong="G1636"\w*, \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w disciples|strong="G3101"\w* \w came|strong="G4334"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w* \w privately|strong="G2398"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w*: “\w Tell|strong="G3004"\w* \w us|strong="G3004"\w*, \w when|strong="G1161"\w* \w will|strong="G5101"\w* \w these|strong="G3778"\w* \w things|strong="G3778"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w*? \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w what|strong="G5101"\w* \w will|strong="G5101"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w sign|strong="G4592"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w Your|strong="G4674"\w* \w coming|strong="G3952"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* completion \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* age?”\f + \fr 24:3 \ft There are two questions: “When these things?” and “What the sign?” The answer to the first is given in Luke 21:20-24. The answer to the second begins here in verse 5.\f*  
\v 4 \w So|strong="G2532"\w* \w in|strong="G2532"\w* answer \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*: “Watch \w out|strong="G2532"\w*, \w so|strong="G2532"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w no|strong="G3361"\w* \w one|strong="G5100"\w* \w deceives|strong="G4105"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*.  
\v 5 \w Because|strong="G1063"\w* \w many|strong="G4183"\w* \w will|strong="G1510"\w* \w come|strong="G2064"\w* \w in|strong="G1909"\w* \w my|strong="G1473"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w*, ‘\w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*,’ \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G1510"\w* \w deceive|strong="G4105"\w* \w many|strong="G4183"\w*.  
\v 6 \w You|strong="G3708"\w* \w will|strong="G3195"\w* \w be|strong="G1096"\w* concerned \w when|strong="G1161"\w* \w you|strong="G3708"\w* hear\f + \fr 24:6 \ft I follow the best line of transmission, with 25% of the Greek manuscripts, in reading “You will be concerned when you hear”, instead of ‘you will be about to hear’ (more or less followed by most versions).\f* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w wars|strong="G4171"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* rumors \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w wars|strong="G4171"\w*; \w see|strong="G3708"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w you|strong="G3708"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w get|strong="G1096"\w* worked \w up|strong="G1210"\w*; \w for|strong="G1063"\w* \w all|strong="G2532"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w has|strong="G1096"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w happen|strong="G1096"\w*, \w but|strong="G1161"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w end|strong="G5056"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w yet|strong="G2532"\w*.  
\v 7 \w For|strong="G1063"\w* \w nation|strong="G1484"\w* \w will|strong="G1510"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w raised|strong="G1453"\w* \w up|strong="G1453"\w* \w against|strong="G2596"\w* \w nation|strong="G1484"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* kingdom \w against|strong="G2596"\w* kingdom, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w there|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G1510"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w famines|strong="G3042"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* pestilences \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w earthquakes|strong="G4578"\w* \w in|strong="G1909"\w* \w various|strong="G2596"\w* \w places|strong="G5117"\w*;  
