\p
\v 24 “\w Then|strong="G2532"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w had|strong="G2532"\w* \w received|strong="G2983"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w one|strong="G1520"\w* \w talent|strong="G5007"\w* \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w approached|strong="G4334"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w*: ‘\w Lord|strong="G2962"\w*, \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w knew|strong="G1097"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w hard|strong="G4642"\w* \w man|strong="G1520"\w*, \w reaping|strong="G2325"\w* \w where|strong="G3699"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w did|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w sow|strong="G4687"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w gathering|strong="G4863"\w* \w where|strong="G3699"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w did|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w scatter|strong="G1287"\w*.  
\v 25 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w being|strong="G2532"\w* \w afraid|strong="G5399"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w went|strong="G2532"\w* off \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w hid|strong="G2928"\w* \w your|strong="G4674"\w* \w talent|strong="G5007"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w ground|strong="G1093"\w*; \w here|strong="G1722"\w*, \w take|strong="G2532"\w* \w what|strong="G3588"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w yours|strong="G4771"\w*.’\f + \fr 25:25 \ft Evidently the third man did not identify with his lord's interests. He served out of fear or necessity, but his heart wasn't in it. He has a negative opinion of his lord and is unrepentant: “here, take what is yours”. He winds up in hell. Are there not many ‘Christians’ today who have a low opinion of God? Who feel that He is hard, unfair, unjust—and who ‘serve’ out of fear or a sense of obligation? If you believe \+nd into\+nd* Jesus you identify with Him.\f*  
\v 26 \w So|strong="G2532"\w* \w in|strong="G2532"\w* answer \w his|strong="G2532"\w* \w lord|strong="G2962"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w*: ‘\w You|strong="G3754"\w* \w wicked|strong="G4190"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w lazy|strong="G3636"\w* \w servant|strong="G1401"\w*! \w You|strong="G3754"\w* \w knew|strong="G1492"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w reap|strong="G2325"\w* \w where|strong="G3699"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w did|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w sow|strong="G4687"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w gather|strong="G4863"\w* \w where|strong="G3699"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w did|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w scatter|strong="G1287"\w*.\f + \fr 25:26 \ft Observe that the owner did not deny the description. The first two servants identified with the owner's interests anyway.\f*  
